[1] Israel ex Ukraine (Cherkasy)
Date: Mon 8 Oct 2018 9:20 AM IDT
Source: The Yeshiva World [summ., edited]
https://www.theyeshivaworld.com/news/israel-news/1600430/breslov-rav-in-tzefas-hospitalized-in-critical-condition-with-the-measles.html


Rabbi Chaim Koenig, the Menahel of mosdos Breslov in Tzefas [Safed, Northern district], is hospitalized in Carmel Hospital in critical condition, diagnosed with the measles. According to the Ynet report, the rabbi contracted the measles following his return home to Israel from a visit to Uman (Cherkasy region, Ukraine].

On Sun 28 Tishrei [7 Oct 2018], the rabbi was placed on an ECMO [extracorporeal membrane oxygenation] machine, which replaces heart/lung functions, and was transferred from Ziv Hospital to Carmel Hospital, where he remains in critical condition in an intensive care unit. Officials report he has a severe viral pneumonia, which has resulted from the measles.

Israel's Health Ministry recently released a warning that persons who traveled to Uman may have been infected with the measles, referring to passengers on both KLM and Air Ukraine airlines, urging them to get vaccinated. The illness appears to be making a return as there are many people who refuse to have their children vaccinated.

According to the ministry, the largest numbers of cases of measles this year [2018] are being reported in Petach Tikvah, with 53. Tzefas is next with 43 cases, followed by Tel Aviv with 22 and Jerusalem with 20.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Uman is a city located in Cherkasy Oblast (region) in central Ukraine, to the east of Vinnytsia. See the following report on the high number of measles cases in Ukraine. - Mod.LK

